note.para:
OmegaT packages are available both in versions bundled with Java, and
  versions without it. Packages without Java rely on a &javaversionlong;
  installed systemwide.

section.programlisting:
files = project.projectFiles;
for (i in 0 ..< files.size())
{
	for (j in 0 ..< files[i].entries.size())
	{
		currSegment = files[i].entries[j];
		if (project.getTranslationInfo(currSegment))
		{
			source = currSegment.getSrcText();
			target = project.getTranslationInfo(currSegment).translation;
			console.println(source + " >>>> " + target);
		}     
	}
}

listitem.para:
The template variables list gives you access to various project
		data and system variables:

		  Simple examples of post-processing commands:


			  Open the target folder in Linux

				xdg-open ${targetRoot}



			  Open the target folder in macOS

				open ${targetRoot}



			  Open the target folder in Windows Powershell

				Invoke-Item ${targetRoot}

section.para:
If the file name is ambiguous, variables of the form
		${nameonly-extension number}
		and ${extension-extension number}
		 can be used.
